<comment datatype='string'>The &lt;i&gt;rpmF&lt;/i&gt; and &lt;i&gt;pslX-fab&lt;/i&gt; genes are cotranscribed, and this is the fist example where lipid biosynthetic genes and a ribosomal protein gene comprise an operon [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/7635191&quot;&gt;Podkovyrov95&lt;/a&gt;]. 
&lt;p&gt;
